        <mxCell id="p04-c97" value="&lt;b&gt;Trace ③.&lt;/b&gt; cron → per-source adapter → normalise into &lt;b&gt;external_events&lt;/b&gt; (+ geohash) → &lt;b&gt;runBuildExternalIndexNow&lt;/b&gt; rebuilds the sharded &lt;b&gt;external_events_index&lt;/b&gt; → clients read the index cache-first and page nearest-first with server-side ordering. Clients never scan the raw feed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Open item.&lt;/b&gt; The &lt;b&gt;attendees&lt;/b&gt; collection-group index is required for the &quot;Going&quot; tab to resolve a user&#x27;s events across all events — verify it exists in firestore.indexes.json before shipping changes to that tab." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fillColor=#FFFDE7;strokeColor=#F9A825;fontSize=11;fontColor=#5D4037;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="20" y="1028" width="1881" height="68" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
