        <mxCell id="p08-c116" value="&lt;b&gt;Blast radius.&lt;/b&gt; Admin functions are the highest-privilege surface in the system (impersonateUser, adjustUserCoins, executeMassAction, adminBulkDeleteUsers). They must be guarded by &lt;b&gt;admin_users&lt;/b&gt; role checks server-side — never by client-side routing — and every call writes to &lt;b&gt;admin_actions&lt;/b&gt; / &lt;b&gt;admin_audit_index&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rules regression watch.&lt;/b&gt; The July-2026 storage/firestore lockdown broke chat-media upload, &lt;b&gt;users/**&lt;/b&gt; subcollection writes and coin-gift notifications. Re-check those exact paths after any rules change; remember rules do NOT cascade into subcollections." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fillColor=#FFFDE7;strokeColor=#F9A825;fontSize=11;fontColor=#5D4037;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="20" y="1835" width="1574" height="85" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
